data.name: latest_manual_review
data.value: SELECT MAX(id) AS `review_id`, conversation_id FROM `review` `review` WHERE `review`.`review_type` = 'manual' AND `review`.`status` = 'published' GROUP BY `review`.`conversation_id`

data.name: latest_auto_review
data.value: SELECT MAX(id) AS `review_id`, conversation_id FROM `review` `review` WHERE `review`.`review_type` = 'auto' AND `review`.`status` = 'published' GROUP BY `review`.`conversation_id`

data.name: difficulty_level_name
data.value:
SELECT levels.*
  FROM app_config
  JOIN JSON_TABLE(
    app_config.value,
    "$.value.levels[*]" COLUMNS (
      `ordering` FOR ORDINALITY,
      `value` VARCHAR(255) PATH "$.value",
      `name` VARCHAR(255) PATH "$.name"
    )
  ) AS levels
  WHERE app_config.system_name = 'labeling.tagging.difficultyLevel.config'

data.name: conversation_details
data.value: SELECT p.name AS workstream, b.name AS batch_name, contributor.turing_email AS assigned_to_email, c.id, c.batch_id, c.colab_link, c.completed_at as completion_date, c.conversation_seed_id, c.created_at, c.duration_minutes, c.maximum_turns, c.minimum_turns, c.number_of_turns, c.project_id, c.statement, c.status, c.updated_at, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM conversation_version cv WHERE cv.conversation_id = c.id AND cv.status = 'published') AS version_count, s.metadata as seed_metadata,JSON_VALUE(s.metadata, '$."Project / Action"') AS seed_project,JSON_VALUE(s.metadata, '$."Technical Domain"') AS seed_technical_domain, ar.id AS auto_review_id, ar.status AS auto_review_status, ar.score AS auto_review_score, ar.feedback AS auto_review_feedback, ar.followup_required AS auto_review_followup_required, ar.duration_minutes AS auto_review_duration_minutes, ar.submitted_at AS auto_review_submitted_at, ar.reviewer_id AS auto_review_reviewer_id, mr.id AS manual_review_id, mr.status AS manual_review_status, mr.score AS manual_review_score, mr.feedback AS manual_review_feedback, mr.followup_Required AS manual_review_followup_required, mr.duration_minutes AS manual_review_duration_minutes, mr.submitted_at AS manual_review_submitted_at, mr.reviewer_id AS manual_review_reviewer_id, mrc.turing_email AS manual_review_reviewer_email FROM conversation c LEFT JOIN project p ON p.id = c.project_id LEFT JOIN batch b ON b.id = c.batch_id LEFT JOIN conversation_seed s ON s.id = c.conversation_seed_id LEFT JOIN contributor contributor ON contributor.id = c.llm_role_id LEFT JOIN (SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() OVER ( PARTITION BY conversation_id ORDER BY created_at DESC ) AS row_num FROM review WHERE review_type = 'auto') ar ON ar.conversation_id = c.id AND ar.row_num = 1 LEFT JOIN (SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() OVER ( PARTITION BY conversation_id ORDER BY created_at DESC ) AS row_num FROM review WHERE review_type = 'manual') mr ON mr.conversation_id = c.id AND mr.row_num = 1 LEFT JOIN contributor mrc ON mrc.id = mr.reviewer_id;

data.name: latest_completed_labeling_workflow
data.value: SELECT MAX(id) AS `workflow_id`, task_id FROM `task_labeling_workflow` `workflow` WHERE `workflow`.`status` = "completed" GROUP BY `workflow`.`task_id`

data.name: latest_labeling_workflow
data.value: SELECT MAX(id) AS `workflow_id`, task_id FROM `task_labeling_workflow` `workflow` WHERE `workflow`.`status` != "deleted" GROUP BY `workflow`.`task_id`

data.name: latest_delivery_batch
data.value: SELECT task_id, MAX(delivery_batch_id) AS `delivery_batch_id` FROM `delivery_batch_task` `delivery_batch_task` GROUP BY `delivery_batch_task`.`task_id`

data.name: batch_stats
data.value: SELECT c.batch_id as batch_id, COUNT(c.id) as total_conversations, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "draft" THEN 1 END) as draft, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "pending" THEN 1 END) as pending, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "labeling-approval" THEN 1 END) as labeling_approval, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "labeling" THEN 1 END) as labeling, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "completed-approval" THEN 1 END) as completed_approval, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "completed" THEN 1 END) as completed, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "validating" THEN 1 END) as validating, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "validated" THEN 1 END) as validated, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "rework" THEN 1 END) as rework, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "improper" THEN 1 END) as improper FROM conversation c GROUP BY c.batch_id;

data.name: batch_stats
data.value: SELECT c.batch_id as batch_id, COUNT(c.id) as total_conversations, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "draft" THEN 1 END) as draft, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "pending" THEN 1 END) as pending, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "labeling-approval" THEN 1 END) as labeling_approval, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "labeling" THEN 1 END) as labeling, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "completed-approval" THEN 1 END) as completed_approval, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "completed" THEN 1 END) as completed, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "validating" THEN 1 END) as validating, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "validated" THEN 1 END) as validated, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "rework" THEN 1 END) as rework, COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "improper" THEN 1 END) as improper FROM conversation c GROUP BY c.batch_id;

data.name: batch_stats
data.value:
SELECT
  c.batch_id as batch_id,
  COUNT(c.id) as total_conversations,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "draft" THEN 1 END) as draft,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "pending" THEN 1 END) as pending,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "labeling-approval" THEN 1 END) as labeling_approval,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "labeling" THEN 1 END) as labeling,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "completed-approval" THEN 1 END) as completed_approval,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "completed" THEN 1 END) as completed,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "validating" THEN 1 END) as validating,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "validated" THEN 1 END) as validated,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "rework" THEN 1 END) as rework,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN c.status = "improper" THEN 1 END) as improper
FROM conversation c
GROUP BY c.batch_id;

data.name: delivery_batch_stats
data.value: SELECT dbt.delivery_batch_id as delivery_batch_id, COUNT(dbt.id) as total_tasks FROM delivery_batch_task dbt GROUP BY dbt.delivery_batch_id;

data.name: delivery_batch_stats

data.name: delivery_batch_stats

data.name: delivery_batch_stats
data.value:
SELECT
    dbt.delivery_batch_id as delivery_batch_id,
    COUNT(dbt.id) as total_tasks,
    SUM(c.number_of_turns) as total_turns
    FROM delivery_batch_task dbt
    INNER JOIN conversation c ON c.id = dbt.task_id
    GROUP BY dbt.delivery_batch_id;
